In "Page Comparison" I would like to be able to directly jump to current version, without the need to call the page history in between. Same when viewing an old version of a page (e.g. v7), I have been using the button "jump to current version" (e.g. v18) in an old confluence version. I miss it; it consumes time to navigate via page history.

Typical (nearly daily) workflow: Via e-mail, I get notificated of the changes during last 24 hours. Wihin the mail, links point to the last change of each page. In the browser, I click "left/previous" (for screenshot see http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+4.0+Release+Notes#Confluence40ReleaseNotes-ImprovedPageComparisonFunctionality) until I reached the last state I know. Now I understood all changes and would like to edit the current page version.

