There needs to be a way of preventing macro code from being pasted into the editor as part of a simple text copy (as described in issue CSP-76287). It is fine to have text style information copied as part of a text copy but not so much the macro code which is hosting the text.

Steps to reproduce. Add the following markup to a Confluence page:
{noformat}
{panel:title=Panel|bgColor=lightblue} 
{table} 
||Col1||Col2|| 
|Foo|bar| 
{table} 

{panel} 
{table} 
||Col1||Col2|| 
|Foo|bar| 
{table}
{noformat}
Switch between the default theme and the documentation theme. When using the Documentation theme, the table gridlines disappear in the table inside the panel

