Feedback from customer:
'If the connection is lost, and Confluence attempts to auto-save, a glaring red message is presented which states "Error saving draft. No draft has been saved." This, naturally, can be quite alarming. So, one's natural instinct is to hit the Save button. Unfortunately, this leads to a "Page not available" error and all unsaved changes are lost.'

As there isn't a lot we can do about the fact that a page can't be saved when you don't have a connection, it would be at least good to guide the user to not to try and save the page unless they definitely have a connection present. Alternatively, if a draft fails you could make it so that clicking 'save' copies the entire body of the document to the clipboard so that lost data can be easily recovered.

