On JIRA, using this JQuery to make a issue search: 
{code}
summary ~ "test+summary"
{code}
And the following XML link location can be retrieve :
{code}
http://mymac:8090/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest-xml/temp/SearchRequest.xml?jqlQuery=summary+%7E+%22test%2Bexample%22&tempMax=1000
{code}
By using this URL in the JIRA issue macro on Confluence(as in the screenshot), the URL is not correctly translated after saving the page and it becomes:
{code}
http://mymac:8090/secure/IssueNavigator.jspa?reset=true&jqlQuery=summary%20%7E%20%22test+example%22&tempMax=1000
{code}
Which give the output of the JQuery on JIRA:
{code}
summary ~ "test example"
{code} 
This cause the JIRA macro not giving the correct output on Confluence.

Thanks in advance for your help.

